  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best way to find out how many people search for specific keywords online?",
  "response": "To determine how many people search for specific keywords online, you can use a combination of keyword research tools, search engine data, and analytics platforms. Here are the best methods:\n\n### 1. **Use Keyword Research Tools**\n   - **Google Keyword Planner**: A free tool provided by Google Ads that shows search volume, competition, and related keywords.\n     - Visit [Google Ads Keyword Planner](https://ads.google.com/intl/en_in/home/tools/keyword-planner/).\n   - **SEMrush**: A paid tool that provides detailed search volume, keyword difficulty, and trends.\n     - Visit [SEMrush](https://www.semrush.com/).\n   - **Ahrefs**: Another powerful paid tool for keyword research, backlink analysis, and competitive insights.\n     - Visit [Ahrefs](https://ahrefs.com/).\n   - **Ubersuggest**: A more affordable option offering keyword suggestions, search volume, and competitive analysis.\n     - Visit [Ubersuggest](https://neilpatel.com/ubersuggest/).\n   - **Moz Keyword Explorer**: Provides search volume, difficulty, and organic CTR metrics.\n     - Visit [Moz Keyword Explorer](https://moz.com/explorer).\n\n### 2. **Analyze Google Trends**\n   - **Google Trends**: Offers insights into keyword popularity over time and by region.\n     - Visit [Google Trends](https://trends.google.com/).\n   - Use it to compare multiple keywords and understand seasonal trends.\n\n### 3. **Leverage Search Console (for Your Website)**\n   - If you have a website, **Google Search Console** provides data on the keywords driving traffic to your site.\n     - Visit [Google Search Console](https://search.google.com/search-console/about).\n\n### 4. **Use Social Media and Forum Insights**\n   - Platforms like **Reddit**, **Quora**, and **Twitter** can help identify trending topics and related keywords.\n   - Tools like **BuzzSumo** can identify popular content and associated keywords.\n\n### 5. **Check Competitor Websites**\n   - Use tools like **SEMrush** or **Ahrefs** to analyze competitors\u2019 keyword strategies and search traffic.\n\n### 6. **Conduct Surveys or Polls**\n   - If you\u2019re targeting a specific audience, surveys or polls can help identify the keywords they use.\n\n### 7. **Combine Data for Accuracy**\n   - Cross-reference data from multiple tools to get a more accurate estimate of search volume.\n\n### 8. **Consider Long-Tail Keywords**\n   - Long-tail keywords often have lower search volume but higher intent, so they shouldn\u2019t be overlooked.\n\n### 9. **Use AI-Powered Tools**\n   - Tools like **AnswerThePublic** or **Keyword Tool** can generate keyword ideas based on user queries.\n\n### 10. **Track Changes Over Time**\n   - Search volumes can fluctuate, so monitor trends regularly to stay updated.\n\nBy using these methods, you can effectively determine how many people are searching for specific keywords and optimize your content or campaigns accordingly.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
